I don't think it's an anomalous effect driving people nuts - I think it's just existential despair at seeing so many different ways for the world to end, without having time for coping/acceptance to kick in. Convince people that they're doomed, and they'll fight back; convince them that there is no fight possible, and they'll sink into apathy. Give them a way out, that seems less horrible than the alternative..?







